Arizona RepublicCol. Tom Leeper ticks off factors that in three weeks have turned the Navajo Nation into Arizona's COVID-19 hot spot.
"There are a lot of issues that made (new coronavirus) a perfect storm on the reservation," Leeper said.
That makes the Navajo Nation third in the country for the number of infections per capita behind only New Jersey and New York.
Arizona National Guard soldiers load personal protective equipment destined for Shiprock, N.M., on the Navajo Nation on April 11, 2020.
(Photo: Arizona National Guard)"We are mostly providing assistance," Arizona National Guard spokesman Maj. Aaron Thacker said.